sec.p:
Of the four initial hypotheses, three received support in the tests conducted:



(ha1) The occurrence of information and knowledge transfer activities of common interest, (i.e., recurrent in terms of independent recollection and mentioning by central actors in the locality) is more likely to be found in non-integrated clusters of enterprises than in integrated clusters;



(hc1) An integrated cluster exhibits a greater variety of information quality attributes indicated by the central actors for individual assessment of each information and knowledge transfer event;



(hd1) A central actor nominated by his peers as a knowledge agent occurs more frequently in integrated clusters.
